Any VM solution will just do NT no sweat, so any pirated or not CD version of Win 2000 or more will just work.


But for 9x... Despite so much software still being win16 and 9x compatible still running, there is NO support! no one runs it except PCem, and that one is not so great! (you need a damn super computer to emulate a Pentium 66 from 27 years ago without lag, not even a high end computer from 2020 will do it), and VirtualBox, Qemu, and Vmware just suck at emulating old hardware.


They should have stick to windows 95, really. And I never though I'll say anything like that!

snippet.textDisplay: Hey.  Loved the content for a pure entertainment point of view, but now im building my own comp, I am having a hard time finding a video for my specific needs. This also goes for all the other channels I watch as well. Lots of vids of "budget builds" and "parts shopping guides" but they are all alot lower then what im looking for. Could you guys do a parts shopping or build guide for a higher budget pc? My situation for example is: professional home builder, have 2 gaming riggs for the wife and myself featuring i7's and 760 and 970 gpus. However my drafting programs run sluggish on it. So I want to replace my gaming rig with a workstation/gaming rig. I dont really have a budget, but since design and drafting programs arnt the most intensive, I dont want to spend 10k on some 3990x just because I can. I want a more realistic build that covers both gaming and some medium level of processing. I dont know if there is much of a viewer base for such a specific thing, but heres hoping. Thanks guys. Keep up the vids ;)
